vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 6
  }
}
title: |md
  ## Scanner Mode FSM
  **NORMAL ↔ IN_STRING ↔ IN_LINE_COMMENT ↔ IN_BLOCK_COMMENT**
  *Mode isolation invariant: no nested mode transitions*
| {near: top-center}
start: ● {
  shape: circle
  style: {
    fill: "#1a1a2e"
    stroke: "#1a1a2e"
  }
  width: 24
  height: 24
}
NORMAL: "NORMAL" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#2d1b69"
    stroke: "#9b59b6"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-color: "#e8d5f5"
    bold: true
    font-size: 16
    border-radius: 8
    double-border: true
  }
  inv: |md
    **Invariants**
    - `is_at_end()` safe
    - `_begin_token()` called
    - No partial token active
  | {
    style: {
      fill: "#1e0f45"
      stroke: "#6c3483"
      font-color: "#d2b4de"
      font-size: 11
    }
  }
}
IN_STRING: "IN_STRING" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#1a3a5c"
    stroke: "#2980b9"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-color: "#d6eaf8"
    bold: true
    font-size: 16
    border-radius: 8
  }
  inv: |md
    **Invariants**
    - `token_start_*` = opening `"`
    - Every char via `advance()`
    - `\` sets escape sub-state
  | {
    style: {
      fill: "#0d2137"
      stroke: "#1a6fa8"
      font-color: "#a9cce3"
      font-size: 11
    }
  }
}
IN_LINE_COMMENT: "IN_LINE_COMMENT" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#1a4d2e"
    stroke: "#27ae60"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-color: "#d5f5e3"
    bold: true
    font-size: 16
    border-radius: 8
  }
  inv: |md
    **Invariants**
    - No token will be emitted
    - `\n` NOT consumed here
    - All chars discarded
  | {
    style: {
      fill: "#0d2b19"
      stroke: "#1e8449"
      font-color: "#a9dfbf"
      font-size: 11
    }
  }
}
IN_BLOCK_COMMENT: "IN_BLOCK_COMMENT" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#4d3319"
    stroke: "#e67e22"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-color: "#fdebd0"
    bold: true
    font-size: 16
    border-radius: 8
  }
  inv: |md
    **Invariants**
    - No token emitted on success
    - `token_start_*` = opening `/`
    - Non-nesting: no depth counter
    - `\n` tracked by `advance()`
  | {
    style: {
      fill: "#2d1f0d"
      stroke: "#9e5c0f"
      font-color: "#f0c287"
      font-size: 11
    }
  }
}
start -> NORMAL
NORMAL -> IN_STRING: |md `"` consumed by `advance()`
`_begin_token()` already called
`token_start_*` = `"` position| {
  style: {
    stroke: "#2980b9"
    font-color: "#aed6f1"
    font-size: 12
    bold: true
  }
}
IN_STRING -> NORMAL: |md **unescaped `"` consumed**
→ emit `STRING(lexeme=source[start:current])`
`lexeme` includes both quote chars| {
  style: {
    stroke: "#2ecc71"
    font-color: "#a9dfbf"
    font-size: 12
    bold: true
  }
}
IN_STRING -> NORMAL: |md **`\n` consumed** OR **EOF**
→ emit `ERROR` at `token_start_*`
scanning resumes on next line| {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e74c3c"
    font-color: "#f1948a"
    font-size: 12
    bold: true
    stroke-dash: 3
  }
}
NORMAL -> IN_LINE_COMMENT: |md `//` consumed
first `/` by `advance()`
second `/` by `_match('/')` | {
  style: {
    stroke: "#27ae60"
    font-color: "#a9dfbf"
    font-size: 12
    bold: true
  }
}
IN_LINE_COMMENT -> NORMAL: |md **`\n` peeked (NOT consumed)** OR **EOF**
→ emit **no token**
`\n` left for main loop whitespace handler| {
  style: {
    stroke: "#27ae60"
    font-color: "#a9dfbf"
    font-size: 12
    bold: true
  }
}
NORMAL -> IN_BLOCK_COMMENT: |md `/*` consumed
`/` by `advance()`
`*` by `_match('*')` | {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e67e22"
    font-color: "#f0c287"
    font-size: 12
    bold: true
  }
}
IN_BLOCK_COMMENT -> NORMAL: |md **`*/` consumed**
peek `*` → `advance()`, peek `/` → `advance()`
→ emit **no token** | {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e67e22"
    font-color: "#f0c287"
    font-size: 12
    bold: true
  }
}
IN_BLOCK_COMMENT -> NORMAL: |md **EOF before `*/`**
→ emit `ERROR` at opening `/` position
(`token_start_line`, `token_start_column`)| {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e74c3c"
    font-color: "#f1948a"
    font-size: 12
    bold: true
    stroke-dash: 3
  }
}
illegal1: "ILLEGAL\nIN_STRING → IN_STRING" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#4a0000"
    stroke: "#e74c3c"
    stroke-width: 2
    stroke-dash: 4
    font-color: "#f1948a"
    font-size: 12
    bold: true
    border-radius: 4
  }
}
illegal2: "ILLEGAL\nIN_STRING → IN_LINE_COMMENT\nIN_STRING → IN_BLOCK_COMMENT" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#4a0000"
    stroke: "#e74c3c"
    stroke-width: 2
    stroke-dash: 4
    font-color: "#f1948a"
    font-size: 12
    bold: true
    border-radius: 4
  }
}
IN_STRING -> illegal1: "nested `\"`" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e74c3c"
    stroke-dash: 5
    font-color: "#e74c3c"
    font-size: 11
    bold: true
    animated: true
  }
  target-arrowhead: {
    shape: arrow
    style.filled: true
  }
}
IN_STRING -> illegal2: "`//` or `/*`\nseen mid-string" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e74c3c"
    stroke-dash: 5
    font-color: "#e74c3c"
    font-size: 11
    bold: true
    animated: true
  }
  target-arrowhead: {
    shape: arrow
    style.filled: true
  }
}
escape_note: |md
  **`\` inside IN_STRING — sub-protocol:**
  1. Consume `\` via `advance()`
  2. If EOF → emit `ERROR`, return to NORMAL
  3. Consume next char via `advance()`
  4. If char ∉ `{n, t, r, ", \}` →
     emit `ERROR` for 2-char sequence,
     **stay in IN_STRING** (error recovery)
  5. Otherwise → stay in IN_STRING
| {
  near: bottom-center
  style: {
    fill: "#1a0d2e"
    stroke: "#6c3483"
    font-color: "#d2b4de"
    font-size: 12
  }
}